column1: Middle Layer Super Output Area (MSOA) domestic gas consumption, 2011

column3: Middle Layer Super Output Area (MSOA) Code

column1: 1 Consumption is given for the local government ward areas Argyll & Bute Islands, Argyll & Islands LEC (Rest of) and Helensburgh & Lomond. These three areas together form the local authority Argyll & Bute,
for which the total figures for consumption and number of meters matches those given in the local authority spreadsheet.
2 Consumption is given for the areas Badenoch & Strathspey, Caithness & Sutherland, Highland, Inverness & Nairn, Lochaber, Ross & Cromarty and Skye & Lochalsh. These seven areas come together to form
Highland, for which figures for total consumption and number of meters match those given in the local authority spreadsheet.

3 Consumption is given for the local government ward areas Arran and The Cumbraes, North Ayrshire and North Ayrshire mainland. These three areas come together to form North Ayrshire, for which the total
figures for consumption and number of meters matches those given in the local authority spreadsheet.

4 Consumption is given for the local government ward areas  West Moray and North East Moray. These two areas together for the local authority North East Moray, for which the total figures for consumption and
number of meters matches  those given in the local authority spreadsheet.
